WHO   — NINTENDO 3DS — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — The 3DS added glasses-free stereoscopic 3-D to a dual-screen handheld, using a parallax-barrier top screen you could dial from flat to deep. Behind it sat dual ARM11 cores and a PICA200 GPU; the headline trick was the autostereoscopic display, later joined by a depth slider and an analog nub.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
